**CMEDIA ReadMe!**

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Open Directory  Opens the directory specified by the user.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

The File types Menu consists of tick boxes that allow the user to filter out file types.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

New category corresponds to the dropdown menu &quot;Category name&quot; above and allows the users to define a new category.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Add Selected To Category adds the current category displayed in the category drop down menu to the selected media type, in the case above &quot;bensound-ukulele&quot; was given the category of &quot;Ukulele&quot;

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Delete From Category removes the selected category from the selected media, in this case it removes the Category &quot;Ukulele&quot; from &quot;bensound-ukulele&quot;



 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

In the comments section, the user can type in the comment box then click &quot;Add Comment To Selected&quot; to add the comment.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

The comment above has been added and greyed out/made non-editable by default to signal a comment already exists.



 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Clicking &quot;Edit Selected Comment&quot; lets the user write in the comment box again if a comment already exists.

Delete Comment From Selected deletes the comment.





 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

The &quot;Save as&quot; button allows the user to save their work (in xml format) and the &quot;Load button allows the user to read that save.





 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Clicking &quot;Load&quot; or &quot;Open Directory&quot; with an already open directory/map will display this warning message.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

The &quot;Add Selected To Playlist&quot; lets the user add the selected song into a playlist. Only allowed filetypes will be added.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

If you highlight an unsupported file type, the buttons are greyed out.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

The &quot;Songs&quot; dropdown shows all the current songs in the playlist.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Clicking &quot;Delete From Playlist&quot; Deletes the currently highlighted value in &quot;Songs&quot; dropdown, &quot;music video&quot; is removed in this example.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

&quot;Save Playlist&quot; and &quot;Load Playlist&quot; let the user save and load the current playlist, separately from the main saves.
